# TP-Link cloud credentials, required for newer SMART-protocol Kasa devices
# (e.g. KP125M) which authenticate before discovery/control. Legacy plugs work
# without these. Copy this file to .env and fill in your values:
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# .env is gitignored — never commit real credentials.
TPLINK_USERNAME=
TPLINK_PASSWORD=

# Optional: a CIDR subnet the server sweeps by unicast on startup and offers as
# the default in the Discovery tab. Use this when your plugs live on a separate
# subnet/VLAN that broadcast discovery can't reach (e.g. an isolated IoT VLAN).
# Leave blank to rely on broadcast + manually-added hosts only.
KASA_SCAN_SUBNET=

# Optional: control devices that no longer accept local authentication (notably
# HS300 strips, whose firmware switched to a cloud-only auth scheme) through the
# TP-Link cloud, reusing the credentials above. Set to 1 to enable. Matching
# models (KASA_CLOUD_MODELS, default HS300) that aren't reachable locally are
# attached after local discovery. Leave blank/0 for local-only operation.
KASA_CLOUD_FALLBACK=
# KASA_CLOUD_MODELS=HS300

# Optional: show an estimated energy cost next to usage. Set KASA_ENERGY_RATE to
# your price per kWh (a number, e.g. 0.18) and optionally KASA_ENERGY_CURRENCY to
# the symbol shown before amounts (default "$"). Applies to every metered device.
# This is a FLAT-RATE APPROXIMATION — it ignores tiered/time-of-use billing,
# service charges, and taxes. Leave KASA_ENERGY_RATE blank to hide cost (kWh only).
KASA_ENERGY_RATE=
# KASA_ENERGY_CURRENCY=$
